Title: A New Approach to Teaching Physical Science
Authors: David P. Jackson, Priscilla W. Laws
Categories: physics.ed-ph
Abstract: During the past several years the authors have developed a new approach to the teaching of Physical Science, a general education course typically found in the curricula of nearly every college and university in the United States. This approach emphasizes active learning through guided inquiry and real-world applications, moving away from traditional lecture-based methods. The curriculum integrates hands-on laboratory activities directly into the classroom setting, allowing students to construct their own understanding of fundamental physics concepts.
PDF: https://arxiv.org/pdf/physics/0608058v2
DOI: 10.1119/1.2150757

